DIGEST
SB 473 Original 2026 Regular Session Carter
Proposed law provides that employers shall allow employees paid time off to vote in an
election.
Proposed law creates an exception if the polls are open for two consecutive hours outside
of the employee's working hours.
Proposed law creates a misdemeanor offense for a violation of this Section.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Adds R.S. 18:1462.2)
